{{Infobox nonhuman protein | Name = Abductin | image = | width = | caption = | Organism = Argopecten irradian | TaxID = 31199 | Symbol = N/A | AltSymbols = | IUPHAR_id = | ATC_prefix = | ATC_suffix = | ATC_supplemental = | CAS_number = | CAS_supplemental = | DrugBank = | EntrezGene = | PDB = | RefSeqmRNA =AF026848 | RefSeqProtein =AAB94680 | UniProt = O44354 | ECnumber = | Chromosome = | EntrezChromosome = | GenLoc_start = | GenLoc_end = }} [[File:Hyriidae - Mycetopodidae.jpg|thumb|Abductin is found in the hinge ligament of bivalves such as ''[[Argopecten irradians]]'' and ''[[Placopecten magellanicus]]''<ref name="Ehrlich"/>]] '''Abductin''' is a natural elastic [[protein]] that is found in the [[ligament (bivalve)|hinge ligament]] of [[bivalvia|bivalve]] [[mollusks]]. It is unique as it is the only protein in nature with compressible elasticity. It is similar to [[elastin]] and [[resilin]], but [[amino acid]] analysis reveals that it has high concentrations of [[glycine]] and [[methionine]].
Abductin is made up of three prominent [[amino acids]], [[glycine]], [[methionine]], and [[phenylalanine]], which are arranged in a [[Pentapeptide repeat|repeating pentapeptide]] sequence throughout the [[molecule]].<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Kelly RE, Rice RV | title = Abductin: a rubber-like protein from the internal triangular hinge ligament of pecten | journal = Science | volume = 155 | issue = 3759 | pages = 208–10 | date = January 1967 | pmid = 6015528 }}</ref><ref name="Ehrlich">{{cite book | chapter = Chapter 19: Abductin | title = Biological Materials Of Marine Origin, Biologically-Inspired Systems | year = 2010 | first = Hermann | last= Ehrlich | name-list-format = vanc | volume = 1 | pages = 319-322 }}</ref>
It has been proposed that the protein could have uses in drug delivery or tissue engineering.<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Su RS, Renner JN, Liu JC | title = Synthesis and characterization of recombinant abductin-based proteins | journal = Biomacromolecules | volume = 14 | issue = 12 | pages = 4301–8 | date = December 2013 | pmid = 24147646 | doi = 10.1021/bm401162g }}</ref>
