{{Unreferenced|auto=yes|date=December 2009}}

'''Tunnel injection''' is a [[field electron emission]] effect; specifically a quantum process called [[Fowler–Nordheim tunneling]], whereby [[charge carrier]]s are injected to an electric conductor through a thin layer of an electric insulator.

It is used to program NAND [[flash memory]]. The process used for erasing is called '''tunnel release'''.

An alternative to tunnel injection is the [[spin injection]].

