{{Infobox dam | name = Çocuktepe Dam | name_official = | image = | image_size = | image_caption = | image_alt = | location_map = Turkey | location_map_size = | location_map_caption = | coordinates = {{coord|37|17|24.33|N|43|34|46.25|E|type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | country = Turkey | location = [[Çukurca]], [[Hakkâri Province]] | purpose = Water supply, military | status =UC | construction_began = 2008 | opening = | demolished = | cost = | owner = [[State Hydraulic Works]] | dam_type = Gravity, [[roller-compacted concrete]] | dam_height = {{Convert|45.5|m|ft|0|abbr=on}} | dam_height_thalweg = | dam_height_foundation= | dam_length ={{Convert|127.44|m|ft|0|abbr=on}} | dam_width_crest = {{Convert|8|m|ft|0|abbr=on}} | dam_width_base = | dam_volume = | dam_elevation_crest ={{Convert|963|m|ft|0|abbr=on}} | dam_crosses = [[Güzeldere River]] | spillway_count = | spillway_type = Overflow | spillway_capacity = | res_name = | res_capacity_total = {{Convert|3100000|m3|acre.ft|0|abbr=on}} | res_capacity_active = | res_capacity_inactive= | res_catchment = | res_surface = | res_elevation ={{Convert|960|m|ft|0|abbr=on}}<ref>{{cite web|title=Cocuktepe Dam construction tender|url=http://www.dgmarket.com/tenders/adminShowBuyer.do~buyerId=1501336|publisher=DGMarkets|accessdate=3 August 2013|year=2008}}</ref> | res_max_depth = | res_max_length = | res_max_width = | res_tidal_range = | plant_operator = | plant_commission = | plant_decommission = | plant_type = | plant_turbines = | plant_capacity = | plant_annual_gen = | website = | extra = }} The '''Çocuktepe Dam''' is a [[gravity dam]] under construction on the [[Güzeldere River]] (a tributary of the [[Great Zab]]) in [[Çukurca]] district of [[Hakkâri Province]], southeast [[Turkey]]. Under contract from Turkey's [[State Hydraulic Works]], İnelsan İnşaat began construction on the dam in 2008 and a completion date has not been announced.<ref name=DSIII/><ref>{{cite web|title=General Directorate of State Hydraulic Works - Hakkari-Çocuktepe and Gölgeliyamaç Dams Construction - Concrete Construction of Dam Body|url=http://www.inelsan.net/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=28:hakkari-cocuktepe-ve-golgeliyamac-barajlari-insaati&catid=8&Itemid=16&lang=tr|publisher=Inelsan|accessdate=2 August 2013}}</ref> Construction on the Gölgeliyamaç Dam immediately upstream began in 2008 as well but was cancelled due to poor geology.<ref name=CNNTURK/>
The reported purpose of the dam is water storage and it can also support a [[hydroelectric]] power station in the future.<ref name=DSIII>{{cite web|title=DSI 10 REGIONAL OFFICE - Van|url=http://www2.dsi.gov.tr/bolge/dsi17/hakkari.htm|publisher=State Hydraulic Works|accessdate=1 August 2013|language=Turkish}}</ref> Another purpose of the dam which has been widely reported in the Turkish press is to reduce the freedom of movement of PKK militants. Blocking and flooding valleys in close proximity to the Iraq–Turkey border is expected to help curb cross-border PKK smuggling and deny caves in which ammunition can be stored. A total of 11 dams along the border; seven in [[Şırnak Province]] and four in Hakkâri Province were implemented for this purpose. In Hakkâri are the Gölgeliyamaç (since cancelled) and Çocuktepe Dams on the Güzeldere River and the [[Aslandağ Dam|Aslandağ]] and [[Beyyurdu Dam]]s on the Bembo River. In Şırnak there is the [[Silopi Dam]] on the [[Hezil River]] and the [[Şırnak Dam|Şırnak]], [[Uludere Dam|Uludere]], [[Balli Dam|Balli]], [[Kavşaktepe Dam|Kavşaktepe]], [[Musatepe Dam|Musatepe]] and [[Çetintepe Dam]]s on the Ortasu River.<ref name=CNNTURK>{{cite web|title=Water retention dams began operation against PKK|url=http://www.cnnturk.com/2012/turkiye/08/23/pkkya.karsi.yapilan.barajlarda.su.tutma.islemi.basladi/674002.0/index.html|publisher=CNNTurk|accessdate=2 August 2013|language=Turkish|date=23 August 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Terror Down|url=http://www.posta.com.tr/turkiye/HaberDetay/Teror-bogulacak.htm?ArticleID=136637|publisher=Posta|accessdate=1 August 2013|language=Turkish|date=24 August 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Planned to be completed in the second dam on the border against the PKK|url=http://www.hurriyet.com.tr/gundem/19088520.asp|publisher=Hurriyet|accessdate=1 August 2013|language=Turkish|date=26 October 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Dams Prevent Smuggling at the Border|url=http://www.aktifhaber.com/sinirdaki-barajlar-kacakciligi-onleyecek-780919h.htm|publisher=Aktif Haber|accessdate=1 August 2013|language=Turkish|date=5 May 2013}}</ref>
